*bcsqrt*

(PHP 4, PHP 5, PHP 7)

bcsqrt â€” Get the square root of an arbitrary precision number

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  bcsqrt ( string $operand [, int $scale = 0 ] ) : string~

Return the square root of the {operand}.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{operand}

  The operand, as a string.

{ scale}

  This optional parameter is used to set the number of digits after the decimal
  place in the result. If omitted, it will default to the scale set globally
  with the |bcscale| function, or fallback to 0 if this has not been set.

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

Returns the square root as a string, or NULL if {operand} is negative.

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 bcsqrt() example

<?php >

  echo bcsqrt('2', 3); // 1.414

<?>

